dataIdInfo.idAbs: The dataset represents settlements of Ukraine. DISCLAIMER: Admin4 is a places layer that does not cover the national extent. Admin4 "Chornobyl" does not nest with its attributed Admin2.

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded by ITOS as a feature class from UNOCHA. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected when possible and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS: 1. As instructed by UNOCHA, ITOS has added parent attribution matching the features' p-code portions 2. Fixed multipart sliver errors in "Stuzhytsia" and "Lubnia" (UA2110017007) 3. Found and fixed 1 overlap error and 167 gap errors. Due to the large number of features in Admin4, some errors may not be found and corrected in this version.
Users should be aware that: - Admin4 is a places layer that does not cover the national extent. - Some small nesting errors exist between Admin4 and Admin2-3. -173 Admin4 names do not have a 1 to 1 relationship between languages. -122 Admin4 names are not unique within their Admin3. - Admin4 "DavydIvtsi" is not Proper Case. - Admin4 "Chornobyl" does not nest with its attributed Admin2.
UPDATE:
1. Admin1 EN name “Avtonomna Respublika Krym” changed to “Autonomous Republic of Crimea”.
2. The name of Kyiv city at Admin levels 1, 2, and 3 was changed to “Kyiv” so that the spelling isn't the same as Kyivska oblast. The change was made for EN name (“Kyiv”), UA (“Київ”), and RU (“Киев”).
3. The name of Sevastopol City at Admin levels 1, 2, and 3 was changed to “Sevastopol” for all 3 languages: EN (“Sevastopol”), UA (“Севастополь”), and RU (“Севастополь”).
4. Admin2 and 3 EN name “Chornobylska zona vidchuzhennia” changed to “Chornobyl Exclusion Zone”.
5. A typo at Admin level 2 for the EN name of Chernivetskyi raion “Cnernivetskyi” was fixed and changed to “Cnernivetskyi”. The fix was made at Admin level 2, as well as in the related fields of admin levels 3 and 4.
